      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PONZI (4) found some support last start but struggled into seventh (19.38), beaten 15 lengths. Was in the money the start prior. Form from his last run is proving strong. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. SANDY BALE (1) had been in super honest form hitting the frame two times on end before finishing fifth (20.46) at Gunnedah last time. Has performed well from this box with a win and four minor placings to his name from eight starts. Likely to be thereabouts. POTENT CARTIER (5) has a strong record this track and trip with two wins and two placings from six starts. In the money last time at Temora (19.11) in a Mix 2/3, finishing a 2.25 lengths third. Looks suited here and can measure up. LATCH ON (8) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
